    <para id="id46089392">
      <emphasis effect="bold">Figure 10. Circuit Diagram of Hartley Oscillator using Op.Amp.</emphasis>
    </para>
    <para id="id42025579">For oscillation:</para>
    
    
    <para id="eip-589">gmR1 = (L1/L2)+(R1.L2)/(RL.L1)</para><para id="id33792965">For large values of R<sub>L</sub>,</para>
    
    <para id="eip-844">gm.R1 = L1/L2</para><para id="eip-893">But gm = Aopen/RL  and /Aopen/ = RF/R1 </para><para id="eip-104">Therefore gmR1=RF/RL =(L1/L2)+(R1.L2)/(RL.L1)</para><para id="eip-690">Typical device parameters of a Hartley Oscillator with fosc = 33kHz are: </para><para id="eip-610">R1=100kohms, RF = 1Mohms, RL = 900kohms, L1=L2=125uH, C = 0.1uF.</para><figure id="id42602327">
